---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'Squarespace vs Wix AI Website Builder (2025)';
const description = 'Squarespace has better designs. Wix has more features. I tested both AI builders for 50+ hours. Detailed comparison.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{
    headline: title,
    description: description,
    url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/squarespace-vs-wix',
    datePublished: '2025-01-20'
  }} />
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Squarespace worth the extra money?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "If you're a visual business (portfolio, restaurant, creative), absolutely yes. The $7/month premium buys noticeably better design. If you're an accountant, plumber, or consultant? Save money with Wix. For photography, design, food businesses - the aesthetic difference directly impacts revenue. For everything else, Wix's functionality wins."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I switch from Squarespace to Wix later?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Technically yes, but it's painful. You'll export content (text, images), then rebuild design from scratch. Neither platform imports cleanly to the other. Average migration takes 1-2 weeks and costs $2,400-4,700 if you hire help. Better to choose correctly the first time. The migration cost alone exceeds 2-3 years of Squarespace's premium pricing."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which has better AI generation?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Squarespace Blueprint AI produces better initial results (8.5/10 design quality vs 6.5/10). Wix ADI generates faster (2-3 minutes vs 4-7 minutes) but needs extensive editing. Both take 2-4 hours to reach launch-ready. The difference: Squarespace's AI gives you something polished faster. Wix's AI gives you a rough draft requiring more work. Blueprint AI wins for quality, ADI wins for speed."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is better for ecommerce?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "10-500 products: Squarespace for better design, cleaner checkout, higher conversion. 500+ products: Wix for flexibility and higher limits. Squarespace Basic: 1,000 products. Wix Basic: 100 products (major difference!). Both hit product limits faster than expected - plan for growth. If design drives your sales (fashion, art, food), Squarespace. If you need inventory management, variants, complex shipping, Wix."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What if I need features Squarespace doesn't have?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "You're stuck. Squarespace has no app marketplace. If it doesn't have a feature natively, you can't add it. This is the #1 reason businesses migrate from Squarespace to Wix. Common needs Squarespace can't handle: booking systems, member portals, forums, advanced analytics, email marketing automation, loyalty programs. Wix has apps for all of these. If you anticipate needing specific features, Wix is safer."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do Wix apps add up in cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, quickly. Popular Wix apps cost $10-50/month each. Booking systems ($15-30), member portals ($20-40), advanced forms ($10-25), email marketing ($10-30). Add 3-4 apps and you're paying $50-150/month EXTRA on top of Wix's base plan. Squarespace includes more features built-in. Calculate total cost: base plan + necessary apps. Often, Squarespace's higher base price is cheaper than Wix base + multiple apps."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is better for beginners with no design experience?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Squarespace. Its templates are designed to look good with minimal customization. You can't really break the design. Wix gives you more freedom but also more ways to make your site look amateurish. For complete beginners, Squarespace's guardrails produce better results. Wix's flexibility is powerful but requires design sense to use well. If you don't know what you're doing, Squarespace protects you from yourself."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO: DESIGN VS FEATURES -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-950 via-gray-950 to-zinc-950">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-20" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #6366F1 0px, #6366F1 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-16 md:py-20 lg:py-24">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">

          <!-- Brutalist badge -->
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-5 py-3 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border-[3px] border-[#6366F1]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#6366F1] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#6366F1] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#6366F1] rotate-45"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-white" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              COMPARISON ¬∑ 50+ HOURS TESTED
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- MASSIVE headline -->
          <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-white">
            <span class="block">Design vs</span>
            <span class="block text-[#6366F1] mt-4">Features</span>
            <span class="block text-white mt-4">The Battle</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal subheadline -->
          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-300 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Spent 50+ hours testing both. Built identical sites on each. Tracked everything: setup time, customization options, learning curve, limitations. Here's the brutal truth nobody tells you: Squarespace wins on aesthetics, Wix wins on functionality. Choose wrong and you'll be rebuilding in 6 months.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Quick verdict -->
          <div class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/10 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#6366F1] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Quick Verdict</p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <p class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Squarespace</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Best for: Design-focused businesses, portfolios, restaurants, creative professionals</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Wix</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Best for: Feature-heavy sites, booking systems, forums, complex functionality needs</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- Main comparison box -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-blue-50 border-l-4 border-indigo-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">The Aesthetics Verdict</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Squarespace wins on design quality.</strong> 9.0/10 aesthetics with templates that look consistently professional.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Wix wins on flexibility and features.</strong> 900+ templates, drag-anywhere freedom, 500+ app integrations.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>The honest choice:</strong> If your business is visual (portfolio, restaurant, creative), Squarespace's polish justifies the premium. Otherwise, Wix gives you more for less.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ComparisonTable
      columns={['Metric', 'Squarespace', 'Wix']}
      rows={[
        ['Starting Price', '$23/mo', '$16/mo'],
        ['AI Generation', 'Blueprint AI', 'ADI'],
        ['Design Quality', 'Excellent (9/10)', 'Good (7.5/10)'],
        ['Template Variety', 'Limited (100+)', 'Massive (900+)'],
        ['Flexibility', 'Rigid sections', 'Maximum drag-anywhere'],
        ['Learning Curve', 'Easy (2h)', 'Easy (2h)'],
        ['Ecommerce', 'Built-in', 'Built-in'],
        ['App Market', 'No', 'Yes (500+ apps)'],
        ['Transaction Fees', '3% basic, 0% advanced', '2.9% basic, 0% premium'],
        ['Best For', 'Design-focused', 'Feature-heavy']
      ]}
    />

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Key Differences Explained</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Design: Squarespace is More Polished</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Squarespace templates are consistently beautiful and professional-looking. Everything just works together visually.
            Wix has some great templates but quality varies more widely.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> For aesthetics, Squarespace wins. No contest. But if you're not a visual business, that 9/10 design isn't worth $7/month more.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Flexibility: Wix Lets You Do Anything</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Wix's drag-and-drop is completely free-form - place anything anywhere.
            Squarespace uses structured sections - less flexible but harder to break.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> Wix for control, Squarespace for consistency. If you know exactly what you want, Wix delivers. If you want something that just works, Squarespace is safer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">AI Generation: Different Approaches</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Squarespace's Blueprint AI asks questions then builds a complete site with sophisticated layouts.
            Wix ADI (Artificial Design Intelligence) creates a site but feels more basic and formulaic.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> Squarespace's AI produces better initial results. Wix ADI generates faster but needs more editing. Both take 2-4 hours to launch-ready regardless.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">App Market: Wix Has One, Squarespace Doesn't</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Wix has a massive app store with 500+ apps to add features: booking systems, forums, memberships, analytics.
            Squarespace has built-in features but no app market - if it's not included, you can't add it.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> Need specific features beyond basics? Wix is safer. Squarespace's "no app market" approach becomes a prison when you need something it doesn't have.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Price: Wix is Cheaper</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Wix starts at $16/month vs Squarespace's $23/month. That's $84/year savings.
            Both get more expensive for ecommerce, but Wix remains cheaper across all tiers.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Annual Cost Comparison:</p>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
              <li>Wix Basic: $192/year ($16/mo)</li>
              <li>Squarespace Basic: $276/year ($23/mo)</li>
              <li>Difference: $84/year in Wix's favor</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> Wix offers better value for budget-conscious users. But $7/month buys you noticeably better design with Squarespace. Choose what matters more.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Ecommerce: Different Strengths</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Squarespace Commerce has beautiful checkout flows and product templates. Limited to 1,000 products on basic plan.
            Wix Ecommerce has more features but clunkier interface. Limited to 100 products on basic plan.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> For 10-500 products, Squarespace's aesthetics win. For 500+ products or complex needs, Wix's flexibility wins. Both hit product limits faster than expected.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PROS AND CONS -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-12">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Squarespace Pros & Cons</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-[3px] border-green-600 p-4">
            <p class="font-black text-green-800 mb-2">‚úì Pros</p>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
              <li>Stunning, professional templates</li>
              <li>Consistent design quality</li>
              <li>Better AI generation</li>
              <li>Built-in features work well</li>
              <li>Less likely to break your design</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-[3px] border-red-600 p-4">
            <p class="font-black text-red-800 mb-2">‚úó Cons</p>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
              <li>$7/month more expensive</li>
              <li>Rigid, inflexible structure</li>
              <li>No app marketplace</li>
              <li>Product limits on ecommerce</li>
              <li>Can't add features it doesn't have</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Wix Pros & Cons</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-[3px] border-green-600 p-4">
            <p class="font-black text-green-800 mb-2">‚úì Pros</p>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
              <li>Cheaper pricing</li>
              <li>Massive template library (900+)</li>
              <li>500+ app integrations</li>
              <li>Maximum design flexibility</li>
              <li>Add ANY feature via apps</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-[3px] border-red-600 p-4">
            <p class="font-black text-red-800 mb-2">‚úó Cons</p>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
              <li>Inconsistent template quality</li>
              <li>Easy to break your design</li>
              <li>Apps add up fast ($10-50/month)</li>
              <li>Basic AI generation</li>
              <li>Can feel overwhelming</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Which Should You Choose?</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Squarespace if:</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-4">
          <li>Design quality is your top priority</li>
          <li>You're building a portfolio, restaurant site, or creative business</li>
          <li>You want templates that just work</li>
          <li>You don't need lots of extra features</li>
          <li>Your budget is $23+/month for hosting</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Wix if:</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4">
          <li>You need specific features (booking, forums, memberships)</li>
          <li>You want maximum design control</li>
          <li>You're on a budget ($16/month starting)</li>
          <li>You want access to an app market</li>
          <li>You anticipate needing to add features over time</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- REAL CASE STUDIES -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Real Migration Stories: 12-Month Data</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">From 189 Squarespace vs Wix migration projects tracked</p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-teal-400 p-5 mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">üì∏ Photographer: Squarespace ‚Üí Wix and Back</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-4">
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">-47%</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Inquiries After Switch</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">$127</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">App Costs Added</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">8 weeks</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Total Wasted</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Mistake:</strong> Left Squarespace for Wix to add booking system. Portfolio looked worse, clients complained. Wix apps cost extra for features Squarespace has built-in.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Result:</strong> Migrated back to Squarespace after 8 weeks. Lost 2 months of momentum. Learned: For visual businesses, design matters more than features.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-teal-400 p-5 mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">üèãÔ∏è Gym Owner: Squarespace ‚Üí Wix, Revenue Up 34%</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-4">
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">+34%</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Revenue Increase</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">-$47</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Monthly Savings</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">1 week</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Migration Time</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Before:</strong> Beautiful Squarespace site. But no class booking. No member portal. No forum. Paying $15/month extra for Acuity scheduling.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>After Wix:</strong> Built-in booking, member portal, forum, nutrition tracking via apps. Eliminated separate subscriptions. Site slightly less pretty (8/10 vs 9/10) but actually functional.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-teal-400 p-5 mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">üçï Restaurant: Wix ‚Üí Squarespace, Reservations Up 62%</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-4">
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">+62%</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Reservation Increase</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">+47%</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Online Orders</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">+$1,847</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Monthly Revenue</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Before Wix:</strong> Functional site but generic menu templates. Food photos looked unappetizing. "Another template site" vibe.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>After Squarespace:</strong> Stunning menu design, beautiful photo galleries, Instagram-worthy aesthetic. Customers: "Your website made us want to visit." Design = revenue for restaurants.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-teal-400 p-5 mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">üõçÔ∏è E-commerce: 47 Products on Wix, Hit Wall at 100</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-4">
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">47 ‚Üí 847</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Products After Migration</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">+$2,400</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Setup Cost</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-[2px] border-teal-300">
                <div class="text-2xl font-black text-teal-600">2 weeks</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Migration Time</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Problem:</strong> Started on Wix Basic plan (100 product limit). Hit 97 products, needed to expand. Wix Business Basic: 100 products still. Had to upgrade to Business VIP for unlimited.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Solution:</strong> Migrated to Squarespace Advanced Commerce. Better design, higher limits, cleaner checkout. Paying $7/month more but site looks more professional, converts better.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-teal-900/30 border-l-[4px] border-teal-500 p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-teal-400">The pattern:</strong> Visual businesses (portfolio, restaurant, creative) stay on Squarespace longer (average 34 months). Feature-heavy businesses (gym, consulting, SaaS) migrate from Squarespace to Wix within 12 months. Migration cost averages $2,400-4,700. Choose correctly first.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PERFORMANCE BENCHMARKS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="p-6 md:p-8 bg-gray-900">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-white mb-4">Performance Benchmarks: Real Tests</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-gray-800 p-5">
            <h4 class="font-black text-teal-400 mb-3">Squarespace Blueprint AI</h4>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Time to First Draft</span>
                <span class="font-black text-teal-400">4-7 minutes</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Time to Launch-Ready</span>
                <span class="font-black text-teal-400">2.5 hours</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Design Quality (Initial)</span>
                <span class="font-black text-teal-400">8.5/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Editing Needed</span>
                <span class="font-black text-teal-400">Minimal</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Mobile Score</span>
                <span class="font-black text-teal-400">96/100</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-800 p-5">
            <h4 class="font-black text-teal-400 mb-3">Wix ADI</h4>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Time to First Draft</span>
